About Grass Journal  &nbsp;
I have always asked questions. For as long as I could articulate thoughts in words, I would ask questions that no one really knows the answers to‚Äîquestions about death, meaning in life, about the universe. As I grew older, I worked very hard to not lose sight of these questions, even when everything else was telling me to focus on what was practical, answerable, and often fear-based.
